The paper discusses a multilingual approach for question answering over RDF data using probabilistic inference and factor graphs. The task falls under the domain of natural language processing and information retrieval, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. Specifically, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as it covers topics related to natural language processing and understanding. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories as the paper discusses machine learning techniques for semantic parsing. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible category as the task involves retrieving information from a knowledge base. Finally, cs.DB (Databases) is a less likely category but still relevant as the paper discusses mapping natural language questions to SPARQL queries for querying RDF data.
